* Install these deb packages:

	pbuilder reprepro devscripts debhelper bsd-mailx fakeroot sudo

* link ./pbuilder.sh to /usr/local/bin:

	link -s /path/to/pbuilder.sh /usr/local/bin/mypbuilder

* Have a look at these files, edit them accordingly:

	/etc/pbuilderrc

* Edit ./pbuilder.sh, change DISTS and ARCHS to what you want to build against. Initialize chroot environment:

	$ mypbuilder create

* Get debian source package and unpack:

	$ apt-get source package_name
or

	$ dget uri://to/*.dsc
	$ dpkg-souce -x *.dsc

* Building debs from a unpacked debian source:

	$ cd package_source_dir
	$ mypbuilder build

If you use git-buildpackage, run:

	$ mypbuilder gbp

You can also use this to build multiple sources:

	$ mypbuilder [build|gbp] /path/to/source1 /path/to/source2 ...

Build results can be found at BUILDRESULT, see /etc/pbuilderrc

* Update should be applied periodically using:

	$ mypbuilder update

* Workflow using git-buildpackage

	$ git-import-dsc [--download [http://*.dsc|package] | *.dsc ]
	$ gbp-pq import
	... apply patch
	$ git add && git commit -m 'patch name'
	$ git checkout master
	$ gbp-pq export
	$ mypbuilder new-patch
	$ git dch -R
	$ mypbuilder commit
	$ mypbuilder gbp
	$ mypbuilder post-build
        $ mypbuilder push
	$ git [branch|tag] patch-queue/${current_tag} patch-queue/master

user    ALL = NOPASSWD: SETENV: /usr/sbin/cowbuilder
